tal of  branches in  countries including  branches in the united states and  branches in mexico the us branches are concentrated in six metropolitan areas new york city chicago los angeles san francisco washington dc and miami in  the united states accounted for  of revenues and mexico accounted for  of revenues aside from the us and mexico most of the companys branches are in poland russia india and the united arab emirates citibanks privatelabel credit card division citi retail services issues storeissued credit cards for such companies as sears conocophillips exxonmobil the home depot staples inc and shell oil as a result of the financial crisis of – and huge losses in the value of its subprime mortgage assets citigroup the parent of citibank was bailed out by aid from the us treasury on november   in addition to an initial investment of  billion a further  billion was invested in the company along with guarantees for risky assets of  billion by  citibank had repaid the loans from the treasury in full including interest resulting in a net profit for the us government contents  history  automated banking card  credit card business  early technology adoption  automatic teller machines  online banking  nationwide expansion  – losses and costcutting measures by parent citigroup   to present  controversies  funding of dakota access pipeline  international operations  sponsorship  in media  see also  references  further reading  external links historyedit view of the northeast corner of william and wall streets the house to the far right became city bank of new yorks first home at  wall street later renumbered as № painting by archibald robertson c   wall street ca  the city bank of new york was founded on june   the first president of the city bank was the statesman and retired colonel samuel osgood in august  with osgoods death william few became president of the bank staying until  followed by peter stagg  thomas smith  isaac wright  and thomas bloodgood  ownership and management of the bank was taken over by moses taylor in  a protégé of john jacob astor and one of the giants of the business world in the th century during taylors ascendancy the bank functioned largely as a treasury and finance center for taylors own extensive business empire later presidents of the bank included gorham worth  moses taylor himself  taylors soninlaw patrick pyne and james stillman  the bank also has the distinguishable history of financing war bonds for the war of  serving as a founding member of the financial clearing house in new york  underwriting the union during the american civil war with  million in war bonds opens the first foreign exchange department of any bank  and received a  million deposit to be given to spain for the us acquisition of the philippines  in  the bank joined the uss new national banking system and became the national city bank of new york by  it was one of the largest banks in the united states by  it was the largest bank in new york and following year it was the largest within the united states in later years it would help finance the panama canal  and stillman then the banks chairman would intervene along with jp morgan and george f baker in the panic of  when the federal reserve act allowed it national city bank became the first us national bank to open an overseas banking office when it opened a branch in buenos aires argentina in  many of citis present international offices are older offices in london shanghai calcutta and elsewhere were opened in  and  by the international banking corporation ibc a company chartered to conduct banking business outside the us which was forbidden to us national banks in  ibc became a wholly owned subsidiary and was subsequently merged into the bank the same year the bank evacuated all of its employees from moscow and petrograd as the russian civil war had begun but also established a branch in puerto rico by  the bank had become the first us bank to have  billion in assets as of march   there were four national banks in new york city operating branch offices also including catham and phenix national the mechanics and metals national the irving national and national city bank charles e mitchell also called sunshine charlie mitchell was elected president in  and in  was made chairman a position he held until  under mitchell the bank expanded rapidly and by  had  branches in  countries outside the united states the policies pursued by the bank under mitchells leadership are seen by a good amount of people as one of the prime causes of the stock market crash of  which led ultimately to the great depression in  a senate committee the pecora commission investigated mitchell for his part in tens of millions of dollars in losses excessive pay and tax avoidance later leading to his resignation senator carter glass said of him mitchell more than any  men is responsible for this stock crash on december   its headquarters in buenos aires argentina were blown up by the italian anarchist severino di giovanni in the frame of the international campaign supporting sacco and vanzetti in following years branches in germany and japan closed  with the bank handling in   billion in treasury securities for war and victory loan drives for the us government in  james stillman rockefeller was elected president and then chairman in  serving until stillman was a direct descendant of the rockefeller family through the william rockefeller the brother of john d branch in  his second cousin david rockefeller became president of chase manhattan bank national citys longtime new york rival for dominance in the banking industry in the united states following its merger with the first national bank in  the bank changed its name to the first national city bank of new york then shortened it to first national city bank in  it is also worth noting that the bank began recruiting at harvard business school in  arranged the financing of the  hollywood film south pacific and had its branches in cuba nationalized in  by the new socialist government and has its first africanamerican director in  franklin a thomas the company organically entered the leasing and credit card sectors and its introduction of us dollar denominated certificates of deposit in london marked the first new negotiable instrument in the market since  later to become part of mastercard the bank introduced its first national city charge service credit card – popularly known as the everything card – in  in  under the leadership of ceo walter b wriston first national city bank and its holding company first national city corporation was renamed citibank na and citicorp two years before respectively by that time the bank had created its own onebank holding company and had become a wholly owned subsidiary of that company citicorp all shareholders of the bank had become shareholders of the new corporation which became the banks sole owner in later years the bank wrote off  billion in debt to brazil and other developing countries  established a subsidiary in poland  and became the worlds biggest card issuer  the name change also helped to avoid confusion in ohio with clevelandbased national city bank though the two would never have any significant overlapping areas except for citi credit cards being issued in the latter national city territory in addition at the time of the name change to citicorp in  national city of ohio was mostly a clevelandarea bank and had not gone on its acquisition spree that it would later go on in the s and s any possible name confusion had citi not changed its name from national city eventually became completely moot when pnc financial services acquired the national city of ohio in  as a result of the subprime mortgage crisis automated banking cardedit shortly afterward the bank launched the citicard which allowed customers to perform all transactions without a passbook branches also had terminals with simple oneline displays that allowed customers to get basic account information without a bank teller credit card businessedit in the s the bank entered into the credit card business in  first national city bank bought carte blanche from hilton hotels three years later the bank under pressure from the us government sold this division by  the company created its own credit card the card known as the everything card was promoted as a kind of east coast version of the bankamericard by  first national city bank decided that the everything card was too costly to promote as an independent brand and joined master charge now mastercard citibank unsuccessfully tried again in – to create a separate credit card brand the choice card john s reed was selected ceo in  and citi became a founding member of the chaps clearing house in london under his leadership the next  years would see citibank become the largest bank in the united states the largest issuer of credit cards and charge cards in the world and expand its global reach to over  countries as the banks expansion continued the narre warrencaroline springs credit card company was purchased in  in  citibank chartered a south dakota subsidiary to take advantage of new laws that raised the states maximum permissible interest rate on loans to  then the highest in the nation in many other states usury laws prevented banks from charging interest that aligned with the extremely high costs of lending money in the late s and early s making consumer lending unprofitable currently there is no maximum interest rate or usury restriction under south dakota law when a written agreement is formed in  macys inc under its former corporate name federated department stores sold its consumer credit portfolio to citigroup reissuing its cards under the name department stores national bank dsnb in  citibank purchased the credit card portfolio of best buy from capital one early technology adoptionedit citibank logo used from  until  in the united states and internationally until  designed by dan friedman from anspach grossman portugal of new york automatic teller machinesedit in the s citibank was one of the first us banks to introduce automatic teller machines in order to give hour access to accounts customers could use their existing citicard in this machine to withdraw cash and make deposits in april  citibank struck a deal with eleven to put its atms in more than  convenience stores in the united states online bankingedit citibankcom was registered in  existing on the internet years before the world wide web was launched at the time it was used for email and other internet interactions but as early as  citibank pioneered online access to accounts using  baud dialup only at first access was through proprietary software distributed on a inch floppy disk following the creation of the world wide web citibank offered browserbased access as well this makes citibank one of the longest term commercialfinancial online operations nationwide expansionedit citibank footprint manhattan chinatown citibank branch new york city citibank branch on michigan avenue chicago in  citigroup the parent of citibank acquired golden state bancorp and its california federal bank which was onethird owned by ronald o perelman for  billion in  citibank was sued for improperly charging late fees on its credit cards in august  citigroup entered the texas market with the purchase of first american bank of bryan texas the deal established citis retail banking presence in texas giving citibank over  branches  billion in assets and approximately  customers in the state in  citibank entered the philadelphia market opening  branches in the metropolitan area in  citibank closed these locations for efficiencydriven reasons in  the company announced a naming rights sponsorship deal for the new stadium of new york mets citi field which opened in  the deal reportedly required payments by citi of  million per year for  years – losses and costcutting measures by parent citigroupedit on april   citigroup the parent of citibank announced layoffs of  employees or  of its workforce on november   charles prince quit as the chairman and chief executive of citigroup the parent of citibank following crisis meetings with the board in new york in the wake of billions of dollars in losses related to subprime lending former united states secretary of the treasury robert rubin took over the chairmanship subsequently hiring vikram pandit as chief executive on november   several days after merrill lynch announced that it too had been losing billions from the subprime mortgage crisis in the united states citi reported that it will lose – billion in the fourth quarter of  in addition to the  billion it lost in the third quarter of  effective november   citibank sold its  branches and  billion in deposits in puerto rico to banco popular in january  citigroup reported a  billion loss in the fourth quarter of  after an  billion write down in march  citibank set up mobile money ventures a joint venture with sk telecom to develop mobile apps for banking the venture was sold to intuit in june  citibank privatkunden ag  co kgaa the companys german division was sold in july  to the french crédit mutuel group on february   it was renamed to targobank in august  after a threeyear investigation by the california attorney general citibank was ordered to repay the  million that was removed from  customers accounts over an year period from  to  plus an additional  million in interest and penalties the money was taken under an electronic account sweeping program where any positive balances from overpayments or double payments were removed without notice to the customers on november   citigroup was forced to seek federal financing to avoid a collapse similar to those suffered by its competitors bear stearns and aig the us government provided  billion and guarantees to risky assets to citigroup in exchange for stock this was one of a series of companies receiving financial aid from the government that began with bear stearns and peaked with the collapse of lehman brothers aig and the gses and the start of the troubled asset relief program program on january   citigroup announced that it was splitting into two businesses citicorp will continue with the traditional banking business while citi holdings inc operates noncore businesses such as brokerage asset management and local consumer finance as well as managing a set of higherrisk assets the split was presented as allowing citibank to concentrate on its core banking business  to presentedit on october   citigroup the parent of citibank agreed to  million civil fraud penalty after the us securities and exchange commission accused the company of betting against risky mortgagerelated investments that it sold to its clients in  citigroup announced it would exit retail banking in  markets primarily in europe and central america in september  citibank exited the texas market with the sale of  branches to bbt in september  citibank announced that it would close its  branches in massachusetts and end sponsorship of a theater in boston in  citigroup incs consumer bank was ordered to pay  million in relief to borrowers for illegal credit card practices the us consumer financial protection bureau said that about  million customer accounts were affected by citibanks deceptive marketing practices which included misrepresenting costs and fees and charging customers for services they did not receive on march   an article in the economic times of india stated that citibank was thinking of closing its  branches in india as digital transactions made them less necessary the articles wrote that citibank was “india’s most profitable foreign lender” on march   the guardian reported that hundreds of banks had helped launder kgbrelated funds out of russia as uncovered by an investigation named russian laundromat citibank was listed among the american banks that were named as having handled the laundered funds with banks in the us processing around  million between  and  citibank was listed as having processed  million of that amount with others including bank of america which processed  million as the bank “handled  million” in laundromat cash on march   an article in the china post stated that citibank’s total wealth advisor twa software system is a “a financial planning system” the year before citigroup had started its citigold diversification index cdi controversiesedit funding of dakota access pipelineedit citibank is one of the lead lenders to the developers of the dakota access pipeline project in north dakota a mile long  kilometers oil pipeline project the pipeline has been controversial regarding its potentially devastating environmental impacts and because the sioux say it threatens their sacred lands and water supply according to a statement by hugh macmillan a senior researcher on water energy and climate issues citibank has been running the books on this project and thats the bank that beat the bushes and got other banks to join in on december th  students of columbia university protested outside of the citibank location on broadway and th street by holding cardboard signs chanting and passing flyers earlier that year the university replaced the oncampus citibank atms with atms from santander bank a bank that has no ties to the dakota access pipeline international operationsedit citibank operates in more than  countries subsidiaries include citibank argentina citibank australia citibank canada citibank china citibank ecuador citibank hong kong citibank india citibank indonesia citibank korea citibank malaysia citibank philippines bank handlowy poland citibank singapore citibusiness singapore citibank thailand citibank uganda citibank uae citibank vietnam grupo financiero banamex sponsorshipedit citibank sponsors the citi field in new york as well as the  atp tournament in washington dc citibank became a major sponsor of the sydney swans in  who play in the afl in the late s first n